<|startoftext|>Question:Should I continue my life as a single mom?
Answer:The question I ask is: Should I still be single?  I do not want to be divorced because it seems to be such a complicated situation.

It depends on your circumstances.  If you feel that your kids may be the cause of your feelings, I would not recommend going for a divorce.  They could be in the same circumstances and be in a different situation.

If you feel that your children are in an abusive situation and you feel that you want their welfare to be given to your kids, then maybe you would consider divorcing.  I have tried to work with this situation since I was younger and in a lot of ways the divorce is a time when I can't be satisfied with the outcome of the divorce.

I have learned a lot over my time in dealing with issues of family and friends.  Some of my children have been hurt so much that the divorce has only a very hard time resolving the issue.  I would not want my kids to stay with other families to help make up for that.  I would get them a second chance at life.

My advice is not to go for divorce.  I know there are some people who will find that this kind of thing can keep them out of the house, so you should go for it.<|endoftext|>
